Package api

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Capabilities
    Defines a set of capabilities for a computer
    Computer<R>
    Defines a machine that takes tasks, executes them, and produces results.
    ComputerCallback<R>
    Callback passed by Computers to executing Tasks
    Proxy<R>
    Define Proxy between Space and Computer
    ProxyCallback<R>
    Callback to be passed to Proxy when it is created that Allows Proxies to comunicate with Space and Scheduler
    Scheduler<R>
    Defines a scheduler that runs on the Space A Scheduler handles the assignment of tasks to PRoxies.
    SharedState
    Defines a state that is propagated to Space, Computers, and Tasks
    Space<R>
    Defines a space that mediates between clients and connected Computers
    Task<R>
    Defines a basic computation task on the system.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Result<R>
    Encompasses results that are passed around between client space and computer.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ProxyStoppedException
    Class for exception that is thrown if the Proxy being accessed has already been stopped.
